# Lab-2
## Design an ALU and verify using test bench
### Verilog Code
```verilog
module alu(a, b, command, en, f_out);
input [7:0] a,b;
input [3:0] command;
input en;
output [15:0] f_out;
reg[15:0]out;

always@(*)
begin
case(command)
4'b0000: out = a+b;
4'b0001: out = a-b;
4'b0010: out = a*b;
4'b0011: out = a/b;
4'b0100: out = a+1;
4'b0101: out = a-1;
4'b0110: out = a<<1;
4'b0111: out = a>>1;
4'b1000: out = a&b;
4'b1001: out = a|b;
4'b1010: out = ~a;
4'b1011: out = ~(a&b);
4'b1100: out = ~(a|b);
4'b1101: out = a^b;
4'b1110: out = ~(a^b);
4'b1111: out = a;
default: out = 16'h0000;
endcase
end

assign f_out = en?out:16'hzzzz;
endmodule
```
### Test Bench
```verilog
module alu_tb();
reg [7:0]a,b;
reg [3:0]command;
reg en;
reg  [15:0]out;

wire [15:0]f_out;
alu m1(.a(a), .b(b) , .command(command), .en(en), .f_out(f_out));
initial
begin
$monitor($time,"input a=%d b=%d command=%b output =%h", a, b, command, f_out);
end
initial
begin
en = (1'b1);
a = 8'd12;
b = 8'd15;
command = 4'b0000 ;
```
